      <span class="answer-first"
        >Proper sizing is based on square footage, volume, HVAC equipment, insulation levels, and
        moisture load — not guesswork.</span
      >
      <p>
        We perform a load calculation for every installation — accounting for home size,
        construction type, number of occupants, and local climate data. Industry guidance commonly
        references 40–60% RH as a recommended indoor range; we typically target 45–50% RH for
        comfort and mold-risk reduction in Raleigh homes.
      </p>
      <p>
        An undersized unit runs continuously without reaching target RH. An oversized unit
        short-cycles and wastes energy. All systems include continuous drainage and professional
        integration into existing controls where applicable — calibrated to 45–50% RH before we
        leave the job.
      </p>
